<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <!-- The above 3 meta tags *must* come first in the head; any other head content must come *after* these tags -->
    <title>Login</title>

    <!-- Bootstrap -->
    <%= stylesheet_link_tag "bootstrap", media: "all" %>
    <%= stylesheet_link_tag "style", media: "all" %>
    
    <!-- HTML5 shim and Respond.js for IE8 support of HTML5 elements and media queries -->
    <!-- WARNING: Respond.js doesn't work if you view the page via file:// -->
    <!--[if lt IE 9]>
      <script src="https://oss.maxcdn.com/html5shiv/3.7.3/html5shiv.min.js"></script>
      <script src="https://oss.maxcdn.com/respond/1.4.2/respond.min.js"></script>
    <![endif]-->
  </head>
  <body>
    <!--Header Start-->
    <nav class="navbar navbar-inverse navbar-fixed-top">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="navbar-header">
          <button type="button" class="navbar-toggle collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#navbar" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="navbar">
            <span class="sr-only">Toggle navigation</span>
            <span class="icon-bar"></span>
            <span class="icon-bar"></span>
            <span class="icon-bar"></span>
          </button>
          <a class="navbar-brand" href="#">Snap4</a>
        </div>
        <div id="navbar" class="navbar-collapse collapse">
         
        </div><!--/.navbar-collapse -->
      </div>
    </nav>
    <!-- Login Form Start-->
      <div class="container">
          <div class="login-container col-md-4 login-form">
              <h1 class="login-heading">Log In</h1>
                <%= form_for(resource, as: resource_name, url: session_path(resource_name)) do |f| %>
                  <div class="form-group">
                    <%= f.email_field :email, autofocus: true, class: "form-control", id: "exampleInputEmail1",  placeholder: "Email", type: "input"%>
                  </div>
                  <div class="form-group">
                    <%= f.password_field :password, autocomplete: "off", type: "input", class: "form-control", id: "exampleInputPassword1", placeholder: "Password"%>
                  </div>
                  
                  <div class="checkbox links">
                    <label>
                      <%= f.check_box :remember_me, type: "checkbox"%>  Remember my account. 
                    </label>
                  </div>
                  <div class="form-group links"><%= link_to "Forgot your password?", new_password_path(resource_name) %></div>
                  <%= f.button "Continue", type: "submit", class: "btn btn-continue"%>
        <%end%>
            </div>
          
        </div>
    <!-- Login Form End-->
    <div class="clearfix"></div>
    <!-- Slider Start-->
    <div id="carousel-example-generic" class="carousel slide" data-ride="carousel">
  <!-- Indicators -->
  <ol class="carousel-indicators">
    <li data-target="#carousel-example-generic" data-slide-to="0" class="active"></li>
    <li data-target="#carousel-example-generic" data-slide-to="1"></li>
    <li data-target="#carousel-example-generic" data-slide-to="2"></li>
  </ol>

  <!-- Wrapper for slides -->
  <div class="carousel-inner login-slider" role="listbox">
    <div class="item active">
      <%= image_tag("login-slider.png", alt: "...") %>
      <div class="carousel-caption">
       We've all heard how crucial it is to set intentions, goals and targets.
Powerful goals electrify us. Clear intentions energize and pull us forward.
Without a clearcut intention, we're reactive and don't get around to doing
the important things when we want them done. Instead, we spend our
time fighting random fires.
Without clear intentions, anything might happen. And usually does.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="item">
      <%= image_tag("login-slider.png", alt: "...") %>
      <div class="carousel-caption">
        We've all heard how crucial it is to set intentions, goals and targets.
Powerful goals electrify us. Clear intentions energize and pull us forward.
Without a clearcut intention, we're reactive and don't get around to doing
the important things when we want them done. Instead, we spend our
time fighting random fires.
Without clear intentions, anything might happen. And usually does.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

 
</div>
    <!-- Slider End-->

    <!-- jQuery (necessary for Bootstrap's JavaScript plugins) -->
    <%= javascript_include_tag "jquery-min" %>
    <%= javascript_include_tag "bootstrap.min.js" %>
    <!-- Include all compiled plugins (below), or include individual files as needed -->
  </body>
</html>
